def: One charged with the performance of a function or office; as, apublic functionary; secular functionaries.
The second, or true, muscular stomach of birds, in which thefood is crushed and ground, after being softened in the glandularstomach (crop), or lower part of the esophagus; the gigerium.
One of the half ribs against the walls in a ceiling vaultedwith ribs.
Burdensome; oppressive. "Too onerous a solicitude." I. Taylor.Onerous cause (Scots Law), a good and legal consideration; -- opposedto gratuitous.

To speak through the nose; to breathe through the nose when itis obstructed, so as to make a broken sound.One clad in purple Eats, and recites some lamentable rhyme . . .Snuffling at nose, and croaking in his throat. Dryden.
Isomorphism between substances that are isomeric.
To rise in clouds, as dust. [Prov. Eng.]
